<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - COMPONENTS - BLOWER
        SPEED-CONTROL RESISTOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BLOWER SPEED-CONTROL RESISTOR</title>
        <para>A resistor assembly (
            <hotlnk document="s16014_4.xml" xrefid="f1601406">Figure 6</hotlnk>) is used in the blower motor circuit to
            provide three speed settings: LOW, MEDIUM and HIGH. The resistor is located in the blower air stream to
            prevent overheating.
        </para>
        <para>High speed for the blower motor is controlled through the high speed relay. In high speed, current to the
            blower motor flows from a 30 amp fuse through the relay.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
